The Police Command in Ogun on Sunday said it had arrested a suspected armed robber, Isikilu Moses, while carrying out an operation in Joju area in Sango-Ota. Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, said in a statement issued to newsmen in Ota, Ogun, that the suspect was arrested on April 8. Oyeyemi explained that the suspect was arrested following a distress call received at Sango-Ota Divisional Headquarters. The PPRO explained that armed robbers had invaded Adebeshi Street, off Joju road, and dispossessed members of the community of their belongings. “Upon the distress call, the Divisional Police Officer (DPO), Sango-Ota Division, SP Saleh Dahiru, quickly moblised his patrol team and moved to the scene.   I watched helplessly as 13 herdsmen slaughtered my husband…     Suspected Yahoo Boy dies after money rituals in Ogun     Man bags 12 months imprisonment for attempting to steal from…   “On sighting the policemen, the hoodlums took to their heels, but they were hotly chased, and one of the suspects named Isikilu Moses, was apprehended. “Recovered from the suspect are one locally-made pistol and two mobile phones belonging to their victims,” she said. She said the Commissioner of Police, Lanre Bankole, had ordered the immediate transfer of the suspect to the state criminal investigation and intelligence department for investigation. She added that Bankole equally ordered a manhunt for the remaining members of the gang. (NAN)